<br>
I'm glad to hear pets will still retain their innate resistances (unless the resistances of the owner are higher). I believe this will help keep the unique abilities native to each elemental, while still allowing those elements to have high resistances in other areas, depending on their master. I just hope this will be considered for PVP as well.<br>
<br>
I've been hearing about hopes for a pet buff report command for as long as I can remember, and you guys came through. Oh yeah, what happened to our /pet who leader command? :P<br>
<br>
These should be great changes, and I'm impressed. <p><br><center><font face="tahoma, verdana" size="1">[ <b>Baron</b> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90407" target="blank">Odibil Lauxes</a> | <b>Arch Mage</b> ]<br>Pain and Suffering tries to strike YOU, but misses!</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=qaedainmagikot>Qaedain Magikot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 735<br> <font color=#333333>(7/19/02 7:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=579.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Thanks</span><hr size=1> /dead <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucalebe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calebe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 196<br> <font color=#333333>(7/19/02 7:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=579.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Thanks</span><hr size=1> Thank you Rich and Scott. <br>
